SHANGHAI, September 10 (Xinhua) -- A survey in Shanghai has revealed that one in eight people in the city suffer from overweight.
The study shows that the 12 percent obesity is close to the standard in developed countries.
The survey was carried out among nearly 14,000 people, including 4,895 adults and over 9,093 young people from nine districts in the city.
It was conducted by Shanghai Medical Sciences University and Shanghai Xiangshan Traditional Chinese Medicine Hospital.
The research showed that the ratio of adults suffering from obesity has reached 12.6 percent, and that of youngsters is 11.35 percent.
